  <prompt>
    Author **ADR-025 (PaneEventBus pattern)** in both forms: the concise AI-optimized form at
    `.claude/adr/ADR-025-pane-event-bus.md` (~100-150 lines, MUST / MUST NOT rules) and the full
    decision-history form at `docs/adr/ADR-025-pane-event-bus.md`. ADR-025 codifies the R2-invented
    multi-subscriber typed-channel event bus that R3 used extensively (`workspace`, `context`,
    `conversation`, `safety` channels with typed payloads and `widget_load` dispatch). This is a
    documentation task that **codifies an existing pattern** — do NOT propose behavior changes.
    Update `.claude/adr/INDEX.md` to list ADR-025.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Architecture documentation author with deep familiarity with the SpaarkeAi PaneEventBus implementation.
    The ADR codifies what already ships in `PaneEventBusContext.tsx`. Source-of-truth is the code; the ADR
    explains the constraints any future caller must obey.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three artifacts: (1) `.claude/adr/ADR-025-pane-event-bus.md` (concise, ~100-150 lines, MUST/MUST NOT,
    binding constraints, code pointers); (2) `docs/adr/ADR-025-pane-event-bus.md` (full form with
    Context / Decision / Consequences / Alternatives Considered / References); (3) updated
    `.claude/adr/INDEX.md` with an entry pointing to both forms. The two forms MUST cross-link to each
    other. Future tasks that touch PaneEventBus (W-4 / W-5 in R4 Phase 4) MUST be able to load the
    concise form and apply the constraints.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec DR-04 + plan §4 Phase 1 A-2: ADR-025 captures the PaneEventBus pattern invented in R2 and
      used heavily by R3 (workspace tabs, context wizards, conversation streaming, safety pane). The
      pattern has shipped, been refined, and now needs explicit governance. Without an ADR, future widget
      authors invent new channels / shapes / lifecycle behavior on every implementation. Style reference:
      `.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md` (recent ADR with the same dual-form structure).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
