  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">ADR-025 codifies an EXISTING pattern — do NOT change behavior, do NOT propose API changes. The source of truth is `PaneEventBusContext.tsx`; the ADR documents the constraints that consumers must respect.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Concise form (`.claude/adr/`) MUST be ~100-150 lines, optimized for AI loading, with explicit MUST / MUST NOT bullet lists. Mirror the structure of ADR-013-ai-architecture.md.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Full form (`docs/adr/`) MUST include: Context, Decision, Consequences (positive + negative), Alternatives Considered, References. Use existing R2/R3 history as the decision narrative.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">PaneEventBus channels MUST be typed (no `any` payloads). The ADR MUST state this as a binding rule, citing the existing TS types.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Both forms MUST cross-link to each other. The `.claude/adr/INDEX.md` entry MUST point to both.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Reference ADR-012 (shared components) in ADR-025's References section — PaneEventBus lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` per ADR-012's shared-lib placement.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/spec.md</file>
