  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read source code">Read `PaneEventBusContext.tsx` end-to-end. Catalog every channel name, every event type, every subscriber pattern, and every typed payload. This is your ground truth.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Read style reference">Read `.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md` to mirror structure / length / tone for the concise form.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Draft concise form">Write `.claude/adr/ADR-025-pane-event-bus.md`. Structure: Status, Context (1 paragraph), Decision (1 paragraph + bullet list of invariants), MUST / MUST NOT rules, Code pointers, References. Target ~100-150 lines.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Draft full form">Write `docs/adr/ADR-025-pane-event-bus.md`. Structure: Status, Context, Decision (with detailed rationale), Consequences (positive: typed channels prevent invented-shape drift; negative: rigid contract for new channels), Alternatives Considered (e.g., custom DOM events, Redux, plain pub/sub), References.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Update INDEX">Add ADR-025 entry to `.claude/adr/INDEX.md`. Add cross-links between the two forms.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify">Confirm: concise form length is 100-150 lines; full form has all required sections; INDEX updated; both forms cross-link; behavior described matches `PaneEventBusContext.tsx` exactly (no invented constraints).</step>
    <step order="7" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Change task 012 status to ✅ completed in `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Document deviations">If any deviation from spec DR-04 or plan §4, write to `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read source code + style reference ADR</tool>
